"'''Shaara and the Sarlacc: The Skiff Guard's Tale'''" is a short story written by [[Dan'l Danehy-Oakes]] that was published in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' in [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]]. It is narrated in first person. In it, a [[Skiff guard/Legends|skiff guard]] under the employment of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] recalls a story about his sister [[Shaara]] encountering the [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]], which he relays to [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]. This happens as [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] are being taken to the [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]] to be eaten.

==Plot summary==
Assigned to escort [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] to the [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Sarlacc pit]], a [[Unidentified skiff guard|skiff guard]] (whose name goes unmentioned) tells the story of his sister, [[Shaara]], and how she narrowly avoided being eaten by the [[Sarlacc/Legends|Sarlacc]] after she outran lecherous [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]] and crashed near the Pit of Carkoon.

However, his sister survived when she was miraculously thrown out of the pit. The skiff guard is not sure why the Sarlacc threw her back, but believes it might be that the Sarlacc will only eat those that deserve it. After more thought, the skiff guard realizes that if this is the case, then everyone should be Sarlacc food.

==Continuity==
In the film [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']], [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] was on the [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] and not aboard a [[Bantha-II cargo skiff/Legends|skiff]] at all, which raises the question how a [[Skiff guard/Legends|skiff guard]] engaged him in so lengthy a storytelling session. The skiff guard was never named in the story and has not been named in any other sources.<ref name="TERC" />

